caption: Came here for a date night and had a wonderful meal outside. They have plenty of sushi options for vegans like myself and standard options for omnivores. Romantic spot!

Absolutely phenomenal food! I had been really craving a great sushi meal  of tasty rolls and sashimi. Being able to walk around the newly renovated Seaport with the river views and Brooklyn Bridge all lit up were an added bonus!

I came here for the first time today based off the good reviews i have seen and i would say its hit and miss. The customer service is excellent they were very kind and prompt with me and its really clean there. I say hit and miss because its a nice dining area and great customer service, but its a little pricy and i didnt quite enjoy my rolls. I got two shrimp tempura rolls with no cucumber and they came to a little over 19$, 9$ each. The tempura reminded me of a “beer batter” fried shrimp instead of the crispy tempura batter that im used to. The flavor was still good, just not as good as i expected it to be. I would go there again although.

Great sushi, friendly service, amazing view of the Brooklyn Bridge. Go on a nice evening and sit outside. Start with the Tuna Ravioli ( tuna carpaccio wrapped around crushed edamame) and go with the Kimono roll ( spicy salmon with truffle oil).  Not cheap, but not Nobu prices either. I ordered Handroll sushi, my mistake as I was expecting rolls. As it was the spicy tuna it was all mashed up with mayo which I learned is supposed to be like that. Taste was not good though. Fish tasted warmer than room temperature. Lack of finesse. The waiter asked me how I liked it and I explained that I ordered the wrong food, I am jetleged etc. he said sorry to hear. It would have been nice if the waiter would have waived one of the rolls that I did not touch and offered me to replace it with something else that is more suitable. I did not happen but I ordered some salmon, avocado sushi roll. They were alright but still missing the finesse. I would not go again. But to be fair for some it might be of good taste. But find it too expensive for what it is

First visit and we had the sashimi plate for $32 which came with 6 types of fish and 17 pieces very generously sliced and so fresh. We also ordered the black cod and that was nice but on the expensive side for the size. The miso eggplant was also too oily. All in all however I would definitely go back for the sashimi plate. Service was excellent and attentive and the vibe was casual with lots of fresh air and views of the back and sides of Brooklyn Bridge.

Nice and relatively comfortable spot and friendly staff.  The evening was pleasant so they had the glass wall opened.  That was fine up until the food started to arrive. This is also when the little fly's started to pay us a visit, but not too too bad. As for the food, it was pretty average stuff you can get from any take out Japanese joint. The happy out fried shumai and gyoza are of the frozen supermarket variety and  the dipping sauce was interesting but found it too salty. For the  main I got the bento box with the salmon.  The sushi and sashimi that came with the box were fresh and sushi rice had the right temp and texture. The salmon was slightly more cooked than I would like but I'm just nit picking up. The salad that came with the box was compose of a well dressed spring mix instead of the usual lettuce which I found refreshing. So why the 3 stars. Well I would have given it 3 and a half if there was an option. Food was pretty average. Nothing wowed us and the quality met the minimum level for a Japanese restaurant. I would say it's a good spot to have a few drinks but for a good quality Japanese food experience it's is not.
